---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Ray Weiss"
  description="Brooklyn wargame designer, running four businesses. Personal site of Ray Weiss."
>
  <main class="px-6 py-24 lg:px-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[65ch]">
      <img
        src="/wargame-counter.png"
        alt=""
        width="48"
        height="48"
        class="mb-6 block h-12 w-12"
      />
      <h1
        class="font-sans text-5xl font-medium tracking-tight text-foreground lg:text-6xl"
      >
        Ray Weiss
      </h1>

      <p
        class="mt-6 font-serif text-xl italic text-muted lg:text-2xl"
      >
        Brooklyn wargame designer, running four businesses.
      </p>

      <div class="prose-body mt-12">
        <p>
          For a decade I tried and couldn't quite learn to code. Then
          AI-assisted tools got good enough. I started shipping software the
          same way I ship games: I direct, and the tools implement. Everything
          on this site came out of that.
        </p>
      </div>

      <section class="mt-20 border-t-2 border-link pt-12">
        <h2
          class="font-sans text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-muted"
        >
          Start here
        </h2>
        <a href="/writing/hammerstein" class="group mt-6 block">
          <h3
            class="font-serif text-2xl font-normal text-foreground group-hover:text-link-hover lg:text-3xl"
          >
            Von Hammerstein's Ghost, In Daily Use
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-3 font-serif text-lg text-muted">
            A Prussian officer typology, used as the operating principle for
            daily AI-assisted work.
          </p>
          <span
            class="mt-4 block font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-link group-hover:text-link-hover"
          >
            Read the essay
          </span>
        </a>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-20 border-t border-border pt-12">
        <h2
          class="font-sans text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-muted"
        >
          Businesses
        </h2>
        <ul class="mt-6 space-y-8">
          <li>
            <a href="/conflict-simulations-llc" class="group block">
              <h3
                class="font-serif text-xl font-normal text-foreground group-hover:text-link-hover"
              >
                Conflict Simulations LLC
              </h3>
              <p class="mt-2 font-serif text-base text-muted">
                Brooklyn wargame publishing. Around thirty board titles and
                three CSR nominations. One SCS release through Multi-Man
                Publishing.
              </p>
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="/devforge" class="group block">
              <h3
                class="font-serif text-xl font-normal text-foreground group-hover:text-link-hover"
              >
                Devforge
              </h3>
              <p class="mt-2 font-serif text-base text-muted">
                Game-development companion for Claude Code. Built for people
                who don't touch git.
              </p>
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="/catalogdna" class="group block">
              <h3
                class="font-serif text-xl font-normal text-foreground group-hover:text-link-hover"
              >
                CatalogDNA
              </h3>
              <p class="mt-2 font-serif text-base text-muted">
                Music cataloging. Hear what your catalog actually sounds like,
                not what you want it to.
              </p>
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="/retrogaze" class="group block">
              <h3
                class="font-serif text-xl font-normal text-foreground group-hover:text-link-hover"
              >
                Retrogaze
              </h3>
              <p class="mt-2 font-serif text-base text-muted">
                Retro image generation with real hardware constraints: NES 54
                colors, Game Boy 4 shades, Genesis 512 colors.
              </p>
            </a>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-16 border-t border-border pt-12">
        <h2
          class="font-sans text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-muted"
        >
          Projects
        </h2>
        <ul class="mt-6 space-y-8">
          <li>
            <a href="/auftragstaktik" class="group block">
              <h3
                class="font-serif text-xl font-normal text-foreground group-hover:text-link-hover"
              >
                Auftragstaktik
              </h3>
              <p class="mt-2 font-serif text-base text-muted">
                Tactical OSINT command terminal. Talked into shape in about
                two weeks via Claude Code.
              </p>
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="/buddies" class="group block">
              <h3
                class="font-serif text-xl font-normal text-foreground group-hover:text-link-hover"
              >
                Buddies
              </h3>
              <p class="mt-2 font-serif text-base text-muted">
                A Claude Code companion and a creature-collection game in one
                codebase. 70+ species, 1,015 tests.
              </p>
            </a>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mt-16 border-t border-border pt-12">
        <h2
          class="font-sans text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-muted"
        >
          Music
        </h2>
        <a href="/music" class="group mt-6 block">
          <p class="font-serif text-base text-muted">
            <span class="font-medium text-foreground">Le Rug</span>, with
            Sweet Bulbs and Butter The Children before that. Brooklyn
            projects from a former life.
          </p>
        </a>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
